         <div>
            <head>“To A Brown Girl”</head>


            <lg>

               <l>What if his glance is bold and free.</l>
               <l rend="i1">His mouth the lash of whips?</l>
               <l>So should the eyes of lovers be,</l>
               <l rend="i1">And so a lover’s lips.</l>
            </lg>


            <lg>
               <l>What if no <rs type="religion" subtype="english">puritanic strain</rs></l>
               <!--We're leaving some suggestions for markup of ideas and motifs.  -->
               <l rend="i1">Confines him to the nice?</l>
               <l>He will not pass this way again</l>
               <l rend="i1">Nor hunger for you twice.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg>
               <l>Since in the end consort together</l>
               <l rend="i1"><name>Magdalen</name> and <name>Mary</name>,</l>
               <!-- This could also be persName, etc. -->
               <l>Youth is the time for careless weather;</l>
               <l rend="i1">Later, lass, be wary.</l>
            </lg>
            <byline>Countée Cullen</byline>
         </div>
